Local Hosting

/*****************************/
/***Laravel installation****/
After downloading the project go to https://getcomposer.org/ and download and install composer. Then go to https://git-scm.com/, download and install git. Go to laravel.com then to the documentation and follow the installation process


/***Vuejs installation****/
Go to https://nodejs.org/en/, download and install nodejs. In your server folder right click and open git bash and run the command:: vue init webpack my-project
You can see vuejs installation on https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/installation.html


/***Set url installation****/
If you are using xampp go to 
xampp\apache\config\extra and open httpd-vhosts.conf and add this


<VirtualHost *:80>
    DocumentRoot "/xampp/htdocs"
    ServerName localhost
</VirtualHost>


Do the above procedures once if you have done it in the other project don't repeat
/*****************************/

##Courier system
<VirtualHost *:80>
    DocumentRoot "/xampp/htdocs/your-path-folder/courier/public"
    ServerName courier.dev (url you want to use)
</VirtualHost>

then run notepad as admin and open C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc  open hosts
add 
127.0.0.1       localhost
127.0.0.1       courier.dev (url you want to use)

save and restart the server
courier.dev will be the url


/***database****/
in the root directory open .env and configure your environment 

DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=courier
DB_USERNAME=database username
DB_PASSWORD=enter your password

go to the database and create a database courier
open git on the root directory and run the command
php artisan migrate
this will create all the tables or use database export courier.sql in the root directory


in the browser the url will be
courier.dev/courier


You can find:
routes in routes/web.php
controllers on app/http/controlles
models on app/
database migrations in Database/migrations